<!doctype html>
<html class="no-js" lang="">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8">
    <meta http-equiv="x-ua-compatible" content="ie=edge">
    <title></title>
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="main.css">
  </head>
  <body>
    <!--[if lt IE 8]>
        <p class="browserupgrade">You are using an <strong>outdated</strong> browser. Please <a href="http://browsehappy.com/">upgrade your browser</a> to improve your experience.</p>
    <![endif]-->

    <h1>-tation</h1>
    <h2>Density of common suffixes in populated areas of Antarctica</h2>
    <p>
      A visual scherzo<sup class="footnote" title="Italian for &ldquo;I jest,&rdquo; &ldquo;scherzo&rdquo; is a musical term that refers to a humorous, up-tempo composition.">1</sup>
      inspired by Moritz Stefaner&rsquo;s
      <a href="http://truth-and-beauty.net/experiments/ach-ingen-zell/">
      -ach, -ingen, -zell</a> and Mahir Yavuz&rsquo;s
      <a href="http://virostatiq.com/data-visualizations/us-suffix-density/">
      U.S. Suffix Density</a> visualizations, both of which are great and
      far less silly than this one. Brighter circles represent higher
      relative density of that suffix in that area relative to other areas
      of Antarctica.
    </p>
    <p>
      Shape data from the <a href="http://www.naturalearthdata.com/">
      Natural Earth</a> project. Antarctic city data from
      <a href="http://www.geonames.org/">GeoNames</a>. Code
      available on <a href="#">GitHub</a>
    </p>
    <p>
      <a href="http://evansheehan.com/">Evan Sheehan</a> 2016.
    </p>

    {{#suffixes}}
    <figure>
      <figcaption>
        <em>{{suffix}}</em>
        &mdash;
        <small class="footnote" title="{{city.name}}">1 place</small>
      </figcaption>
      <svg width="388" height="388">
        {{#circles}}
        <circle cx="{{x}}" cy="{{y}}" r="{{r}}"></circle>
        {{/circles}}
        <circle cx="{{city.x}}" cy="{{city.y}}" r="{{city.r}}"
            class="city">
          <title>{{city.name}}</title>
        </circle>
      </svg>
    </figure>
    {{/suffixes}}

    <footer>
      <hr />
      <p>
        Fonts:
        <a href="http://cargocollective.com/hanken/HK-Grotesk-Open-Source-Font">
        HK Grotesk</a> by Hanken and
        <a href="http://www.fontsquirrel.com/fonts/noto-serif">Noto
        Serif</a> by Google.
      </p>
    </footer>
  </body>
</html>
